data.text:
As of May 2, 257.7 million people have received at least one dose of a #COVID19 vaccine. Of those, 219.8 million are fully vaccinated. More than 100.7 million people have received a COVID-19 booster dose.

Find a COVID-19 vaccine or booster near you: https://t.co/xbvNiaVJKV. https://t.co/tOShsscVjD

As your children catch up on trying to climb to the top, make sure they’re caught up on routine vaccinations by talking to their doctor. https://t.co/hcvlhZVMkj
#VaccinesWork https://t.co/pAalMEKTXl

More than 100 million people in the US have received their first #COVID19 booster. Protect yourself by staying up to date with COVID-19 vaccines and boosters, even if you've already had COVID-19. Learn more in this week's COVID Data Tracker Weekly Review: https://t.co/F4bAyObDp1. https://t.co/tIE31IWHuk

Have a weakened immune system? If you're 12 yrs & up, here’s how to stay up to date on mRNA #COVID19 vaccines for best protection:
1. Complete 3 dose primary series
2. Receive at least 1 booster
3. Ask your doctor if a 2nd booster is right for you

More: https://t.co/Iq5JmSoATe https://t.co/OHwM5ZbruQ

Viruses are constantly changing, creating new variants. Protect yourself against the virus that causes #COVID19 by staying up to date on your COVID-19 vaccines. This can help slow the emergence of new variants. Learn more about variants where you live: https://t.co/8x4EqpiRpT. https://t.co/UKB48eyNfd

As of April 28, 2022, more than 98% of the U.S. population lives in a location with a low or medium #COVID19 Community Level. 

Find your COVID-19 Community Level: https://t.co/w3365V9Zr4. https://t.co/buNbyzgh1F

The latest MMWR Weekly #COVID19 Briefing is live. This episode covers 4 reports, including reports highlighting hospitalizations of children ages 5–11 with COVID-19, vaccination coverage among children in kindergarten and more. Listen & subscribe: https://t.co/I9Zs1YI5zf. https://t.co/lUoqtjNFJC

CDC study shows higher county-level #COVID19 vaccine coverage was associated with fewer cases and deaths. 

Stay up to date on your COVID-19 vaccines. Read the study: https://t.co/aYgzkoszpA. https://t.co/3RbuZbPsKa

New data indicate that completing a 2-dose primary series of an mRNA #COVID19 vaccine (Pfizer-BioNTech or Moderna) during pregnancy can protect babies younger than 6 months from hospitalization due to COVID-19. Learn more: https://t.co/pBVlI6STf8. https://t.co/YCGcoY9aqB
As of April 25, 2022, national forecasts predict 600–7,000 new #COVID19 hospitalizations will likely be reported on May 20. More: https://t.co/Xys80ZGlxV. https://t.co/sLq8aMi3OS
